</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
PASSIVE SMOKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The article "Headlines and High Anxiety" (by David Shaw, Sept. 11) quotes an 
analyst of the Office of Technology Assessment on the topic of passive 
smoking.I am writing to correct a possible misimpression that that statement 
reflects OTA's position or findings. 
</P>
<P>
 OTA and its staff do not take positions in areas we have not studied. We have 
not conducted any relevant studies on passive smoking that would allow us to 
take a position in regard to its health effects or about EPA's regulatory 
stance, and therefore the agency and its staff have no official position on 
these matters. 
</P>
<P>
 ROGER C. HERDMAN MD 
</P>
<P>
 OTA Director, Washington 
</P>
</TEXT>
