<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: TWO LUNKER CATFISH ATTEST TO IRVINE'S STOCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Long Beach anglers are not about to argue the theory that big fish hang 
out together. 
</P>
<P>
 Damian Schenewark pulled the biggest fish of the year from Irvine Lake, a 
48-pound catfish. Moments later, Mark Lawler, fishing on the same boat, landed 
a 45-pounder. 
</P>
<P>
 Both fish were released after being weighed, and for that the anglers each 
received a $100 "conservation award." 
</P>
