</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County officials Tuesday welcomed a donation of more than $11,000 from 
the Ojai Valley Friends of the Library to extend the hours of operation at 
three area branches. 
</P>
<P>
 The approval of the donation included an agreement with the city of Ojai that 
spells out the terms of a city contribution of more than $25,000 to keep the 
libraries open longer than the county could otherwise afford. 
</P>
<P>
 "These funds will allow the Oak View, Meiners Oak and Ojai libraries to be 
open a few more hours a week," county Library Services Agency Director Dixie 
Adeniran told supervisors Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the agreement, the Ojai library will be open 40 hours a week, while the 
two smaller branches will increase their hours from 16 to 19 each week through 
June, 1995. JEFF McDONALD 
