<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; 3 STUDENTS REPORT BEING CHASED, SHOT AT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A carload of suspected gang members chased three Simi Valley high school 
youths in another vehicle and fired a handgun at them, striking their car, Simi 
Valley police said Tuesday. The students, a 17-year-old and two 16-year-olds, 
were approaching Erringer Road from eastbound Patricia Avenue about 3 a.m. 
Sunday when the confrontation occurred, Lt. Tony Harper said. 
</P>
<P>
 The other car, a small, dark-colored vehicle, pulled alongside and several 
occupants flashed gang signs at the students, who are not involved with gangs, 
Harper said. 
</P>
<P>
 To avoid conflict, the students drove away but were followed by the other car, 
from which someone subsequently fired a handgun, Harper said. The students' car 
was struck once. 
</P>
<P>
 The students, who did not report the incident until Tuesday, attend Simi 
Valley High School, Royal High and the Simi Valley Adult School, he said. GREG 
RIPPEE 
</P>
