<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRUCKER CRITICALLY INJURED IN HIT-RUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By IRA E. STOLL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 65-year-old Oklahoma truck driver was in critical condition Tuesday night 
after being hit by a car while walking along Lewis Road in Camarillo. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura County sheriff's deputies were investigating the hit-and-run accident, 
which occurred about 6:50 p.m. Sheriff's Lt. Gary Cook said the car had been 
recovered, but the driver had fled the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident victim, Robert Sullins of Pawnee, Okla., was undergoing surgery 
at Pleasant Valley Hospital late Tuesday, a hospital spokesman said. IRA E. 
STOLL 
</P>
