<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; GARDNER SPARKS SAN CLEMENTE TO WATER POLO VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GABE LACQUES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 San Clemente, ranked No. 1 in Southern Section Division I, jumped to a 
six-goal halftime lead, then got several key saves from Gabe Gardner to beat 
No. 2 Long Beach Wilson, 10-6, in a nonleague water polo match Tuesday at 
Saddleback College. 
</P>
<P>
 Gardner, who finished with 20 saves, found himself in several one-on-one 
situations with Wilson's Pat Cochran, considered one of the top players in the 
state.Their most crucial confrontation occurred with 1 minute 40 seconds left 
to play, and Wilson trailing, 9-6. 
</P>
<P>
 Cochran stole the ball at mid-pool and drove in on Gardner. Cochran tried to 
loft the ball over Gardner's head, but Gardner extended his 6-foot-9 frame to 
palm the ball. 
</P>
<P>
 Colin Shaughnessy and Jimmy Farley scored two goals each as San Clemente 
(13-1) led, 6-1, after one quarter. The Tritons led, 7-1, at halftime, and, 
8-4, entering the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 A goal by Cochran with 5:56 remaining pulled Wilson (10-2) to within 8-6 with 
5:56 left, but Shaughnessy scored two minutes later, and capped the scoring 
with a goal with one second left. His four goals led the Tritons. 
</P>
<P>
 The two teams could meet again this weekend at the Southern California 
Invitational at Long Beach State. GABE LACQUES 
</P>
</TEXT>
