<TEXT>
<P>
 GIRLS 
</P>
<P>
 Kim Mortensen 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Thousand Oaks 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Cross-country 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Junior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Mortensen, who finished fifth in the 3,200 meters in the 
State track and field championships in June, has won four of five races this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Mortensen won two races last week, including Saturday's 
South Valley Invitational at Huntington Beach Central Park. She timed 18 
minutes 33 seconds over the three-mile course, good for a 40-second victory, 
and propelled Thousand Oaks, the No. 1-ranked team in the state, to a runaway 
victory. "Individually, I haven't really set any particular goals for myself 
this season," Mortensen said. "But as a team, we want to finish first in (the 
State Division I championships)." 
</P>
