<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 BOYS 
</P>
<P>
 Ignacio Brache 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Village Christian 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Football 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Brache, a soccer player since his youth who first kicked a 
football three years ago, has kicked eight field goals in the Crusaders' first 
five games and leads the team in scoring with 30 points. He is averaging 39.8 
yards a punt and is being recruited by Washington and Southern Methodist. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Brache tied a Southern Section record last week by kicking 
five field goals in a game. He converted from 35, 42, 48, 55 and 56 yards in 
the Crusaders' 29-14 victory over Southern California Christian. A 32-yard 
attempt was blocked. His 56-yard field goal set a Division X record, breaking 
the record (set by Brache last year) by two yards. 
</P>
