</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sophomore defensive back K.C. Cullum of Crespi High will not play football 
again after suffering a broken neck in last week's 26-24 loss to St. 
Bernard.Cullum, younger brother of senior tackle Kane Cullum, felt a twinge 
during a third-quarter collision. 
</P>
<P>
 The injury is not serious and Cullum is expected to make a complete recovery, 
Crespi Coach Tim Lins said. 
</P>
<P>
 La Canada High running back Ray Lee, the Spartans' leading rusher (269 yards, 
three touchdowns) and receiver (19 catches, 142 yards), will miss the rest of 
the season because of a broken clavicle suffered against Hoover. 
