<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: YOUTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI K; HOLLY J. WAGNER, lan, ; ALAN EYERLY, LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * News for the 18-and-under crowd 
</P>
<P>
 LA HABRA 
</P>
<P>
 Sonora Senior Is Youth of Year 
</P>
<P>
 Audie Contreras, a Sonora High School senior, has been named Youth of the Year 
by the La Habra Area Chamber of Commerce for his volunteer work in the 
community and at school. 
</P>
<P>
 The 18-year-old Contreras, who is the public address announcer for many Sonora 
athletic events, volunteers his time at the Boys and Girls Club, La Habra Leo 
Club and La Habra Host Lions Club. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 PLACENTIA 
</P>
<P>
 El Camino Senior on Traffic Safety Panel 
</P>
<P>
 Melissa Badillo, an El Camino High School senior, was recently appointed teen 
representative of Placentia's Traffic Safety Committee. 
</P>
<P>
 Badillo was appointed to a two-year term on the panel, which advises the City 
Council on regulating car, bicycle and pedestrian traffic. 
</P>
<P>
 Badillo, 18, was nominated by her school principal and selected after an 
interview with the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 ANAHEIM 
</P>
<P>
 Servite Sophomore Becomes Eagle Scout 
</P>
<P>
 Victor Santiago Echevarria, a Servite High School sophomore, has qualified to 
be an Eagle Scout, the highest rank in the Boy Scouts of America. 
</P>
<P>
 A public ceremony recognizing his achievement was held last month at St. 
Cecilia Catholic Church in Tustin. 
</P>
<P>
 Echevarria, 15, is a member of Troop 323 in Tustin. The Scoutmaster is Ed 
Ferrer. Echevarria's Eagle Scout project involved trail building and soil 
erosion prevention at Oak Canyon Nature Center in Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 LAGUNA HILLS 
</P>
<P>
 Jam Session Planned for Garage Bands 
</P>
<P>
 Are you and your friends looking for a chance to show off your musical 
talents? The city of Laguna Hills has just the thing for you. 
</P>
<P>
 The Recreation Department is seeking youth bands for the Teen Garage Band Jam 
Session scheduled for Nov. 19. 
</P>
<P>
 If you want to join in the fun and wow fellow teens with your drum beats or 
guitar riffs, deliver a demo tape of your band's music to the city by Nov. 4. 
</P>
<P>
 The session will run from 8 to 11 p.m. at the recreation center. To receive an 
entry form, call the Recreation Department at (714) 707-2686. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 PLACENTIA 
</P>
