<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; HALLOWEEN EVENTS SET AT LIBRARY BRANCHES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Orange County Public Library will commemorate Halloween with a variety of 
activities at branches around the county. 
</P>
<P>
 On Oct. 20, a Halloween crafts class and fair will take place at the Cypress 
Branch, 5331 Orange Ave.The class is at 3:30 p.m. and is designed for children 
age 6 to 12. 
</P>
<P>
 Storyteller Angela Klingler will recite some Halloween stories Oct. 26 at 3 
p.m. at the Laguna Beach branch, 363 Glennyre St. 
</P>
<P>
 That same day, storyteller Michael McCarty will present a Halloween Family 
Program at 7 p.m. at Heritage Park Regional Library, 14361 Yale Ave. in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dana Niguel branch library will host Halloween Pajama Story Time at 7 p.m. 
Oct. 26. The branch is at 33841 Niguel Road in Dana Point. 
</P>
<P>
 On Oct. 27, the San Juan Capistrano Regional Library will present a Halloween 
parade at 3:30 p.m. Participants are asked to wear costumes. The library is at 
31495 El Camino Real in San Juan Capistrano. 
</P>
<P>
 The Crown Valley branch library will present a Halloween puppet show Oct. 27 
at 9:30 a.m. The branch is at 30341 Crown Valley Parkway in Laguna Niguel. 
SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
