<P>
BUILDUP IN THE PERSIAN GULF; PROBE OF TUSTIN MARINE'S DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 U.S. Marine officials are investigating the death of a Tustin-based Marine who 
apparently drowned last week when he fell off the amphibious assault ship 
Tripoli, which was speeding toward the Persian Gulf. 
</P>
<P>
 Cpl. Steven Mosier, 20, a technician who had been based at the Marine Corps 
Air Station in Tustin for about a year, fell overboard about 9:45 p.m. Friday, 
Marine officials said. Divers searched the waters for 24 hours but were unable 
to recover Mosier's body. 
</P>
<P>
 Mosier apparently fell and struck his head on a landing deck while working on 
a helicopter, Marine officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Mosier originally was from Winne, Ark. 
</P>
