<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: FULLERTON; GOP KEEPS OFFICES AFTER DEAL IS STRUCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bushala Brothers Inc. has decided to allow county Republicans to stay in the 
office space the company donated to further the party's goals. 
</P>
<P>
 The company had sent the Orange County Republican Central Committee a 24-hour 
eviction notice Monday, but an agreement was struck Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Anthony N. Bushala said his father, George, first thought the committee would 
be working for the reelection of Rep. Ed Royce (R-Fullerton). But the GOP 
headquarters was run by Lois Godfrey, wife of City Council candidate Peter 
Godfrey. 
</P>
<P>
 Bushala alleged that callers were being urged by the committee to support 
Peter Godfrey. Bushala said the family was outraged because his family supports 
Dave Zenger, a Republican who is challenging Peter Godfrey. 
</P>
<P>
 Lois Godfrey, who was serving as co-chairwoman of the committee, denied that 
she or any other committee member ever told callers to vote for her husband. 
But she resigned as part of the agreement.MIMI KO 
</P>
</TEXT>
