METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LONG BEACH; REAL ESTATE 
AGENT UNHURT IN BOMBING OF HIS CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An eight-inch bomb damaged a Long Beach real estate agent's car Tuesday, but 
he escaped without a scratch. 
</P>
<P>
 The blast occurred about 9 a.m. in the 700 block of East Ocean Boulevard, said 
Long Beach police spokeswoman Margarita DeWitt. 
</P>
<P>
 The apparent intended victim, commercial agent Lloyd Ikerd, was shaken up but 
otherwise unhurt.  
</P>
<P>
 "The car was just totally blown up," Ikerd said. Asked if he knew who would 
target him, Ikerd said: "I have no idea."  
</P>
<P>
 Police said the device was about eight inches long and had been placed under 
the passenger side of the car. The explosion blew off the car's hubcaps and 
front grill and caused the air bag to deploy, according to KCBS-Channel 2. 
</P>
