<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; STUDENTS TO ATTEND JOB FAIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 High school students from the county will participate in the Career 
Opportunity Fair on Oct. 26 in Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
 The fair is designed to give vocational education students a chance to meet 
potential employers and learn about the job market. 
</P>
<P>
 A variety of companies and organizations are scheduled to attend the event 
including the Chrysler Corp., Toyota, the Auto Club and the Army and Navy. It 
is sponsored by National Hot Rod Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 Students will learn about what jobs are available and the kinds of skills and 
education needed to get hired, said Angie Brown, spokeswoman for the 
association. 
</P>
<P>
 Students and teachers from more than a dozen Orange County high schools are 
scheduled to attend the event, Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 Students from University High School in Irvine, Edison High School in 
Huntington Beach and Estancia High School in Costa Mesa, as well as schools in 
Anaheim, Westminster, Fountain Valley, Lake Forest, La Habra, Fullerton, 
Mission Viejo and Villa Park, will attend. 
</P>
<P>
 The fair will include a hot-rod car show and a contest in which schools show 
off their automotive repair skills. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information on the event, call (818) 914-4761. SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</TEXT>
