<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Don't expect the next bank heist movie to be filmed at your local branch. 
</P>
<P>
 While Los Angeles is considered the bank robbery capital of the United States, 
neighboring Orange County has far fewer of these crimes. 
</P>
<P>
 Bank robbers in Orange County net less than $1 million each year, according to 
the California Department of Justice. 
</P>
<P>
 The number of bank robberies increased substantially from 1990 to 1991 but has 
declined gradually in the past two years. Today 
</P>
<P>
 Does your child have library-o-phobia? 
</P>
<P>
 You might be able to cure it by having your fourth- to sixth-grader attend the 
"Where in the Library is Carmen SanDiego?" workshop at the Newport Beach 
Central Library. 
</P>
<P>
 Starting at 3:30 p.m., children will learn how to use CD-ROM products, such as 
the World Book and Dinosaur Encyclopedias. The free sessions will continue the 
next two Wednesdays.  
</P>
<P>
 The library is at 1000 Avocado Ave. Information: (714) 717-3800. Bank 
Robberies Decline 1993: 249 
