<HEADLINE>
<P>
LIBRARY TO CELEBRATE 75TH ANNIVERSARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 History buffs in North County can indulge their passion at the Placentia 
Library District's 75th anniversary party at 1 p.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Public television show host Huell Howser will be the guest speaker for the 
event, which celebrates the library's humble beginnings in 1919.One resident 
gained the support of neighbors and the Orange County Board of Supervisors to 
form the district. 
</P>
<P>
 Featured will be a display of winning photos from an amateur photography 
contest, a montage of library milestones with newspaper clippings about each 
event, a parade of storybook characters, recognition of some of Placentia's 
75-year-old residents and dedication of the library's History Room. 
</P>
<P>
 Longtime residents have donated artifacts for display in the history room. The 
city's Historical Committee will catalogue, organize and operate the roomful of 
"Placentiana." 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton instructor Joseph Arnold will give readings from oral 
histories, sampling stories from pioneers, industrialists and residents. 
Longtime Placentia historian, author and former librarian Virginia Carpenter 
will be honored. 
</P>
<P>
 The celebration will take place at the Placentia Civic Center complex, 401 E. 
Chapman Ave. The event is free, but donations will be accepted to support the 
"adopt-a-book" program. Information: (714) 528-8248. 
</P>
