<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: BANKING & FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 T-Bill Rates Mixed: The Treasury Department sold $13 billion of new 
three-month bills at an average discount rate of 4.92%, the same as last 
week.Another $13.1 billion of new six-month bills were sold at an average 
discount rate of 5.34%, down from 5.38% last week. The six-month bill rate was 
the lowest since it averaged 5.22% on Sept. 26. 
</P>
<P>
 The new discount rates understate the actual return to investors: 5.05% for 
three-month bills, with a $10,000 bill selling for $9,875.60, and 5.57% for a 
six-month bill selling for $9,730.00. The discount rate reflects the price 
discount received when government securities are purchased at less than face 
value. 
</P>
